cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the concept of threat intelligence sharing and the risks and benefits associated with it. It also introduces the notion of quality of indicators for assessing the level of contribution by participants in information sharing for threat intelligence. The paper utilizes tools from the machine learning literature for quality assessment, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI and cs.LG. Additionally, the paper discusses security and privacy concerns, which aligns with the sub-category of cs.CR. The paper also discusses the empirical study conducted, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI and cs.SE.
